  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>The eyeblink of the Startle reflex is measured.</measure>
    <time_frame>The startle reflex will be measured in relation to picture presentations during the experiment (e.g. day 1).</time_frame>
    <description>The startle reflex is potentiated when participants are influenced by negative emotions. Accordingly, startle will be measured in relation to picture presentation to gauge the emotional effect of the pictures. It is expected that the ASD group will show fear potentiated startle to pictures of human faces.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
